    "created_at": "2016-12-15T23:43:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-12-15T23:43:10Z",
    "body": "I am wondering if this is the expected behavior on Mac where modal dialog is supposed to block until current event is processed.\r\nOne example is the Terminal on Mac. Say we have 2 tabs open. Open `vi` editor in one of them and keep the focus. Pressing `cmd-w` triggers a confirmation modal dialog. Pressing `cmd-q` afterwards does not quite application."
